installationInstructions.author: James from SHENANDOAH, TX
installationInstructions.title: Lower tines rusted out and would not hold dishes to clean them properly.
installationInstructions.content: Removed two rusted tines lines, then I unclipped the stabilizers, installed four other  positioning clips, put the two adjustable tines in the two vertical plastic stabilizers at the ends of the lower baskets. Worked like a charm and all is good. May I suggest using stainless steel or more nickel in the iron used in the basket or a thicker or more durable plastic in the tines.
